3.10	Zygi	Zygi	Zygi is a small village located in the south of Cyprus between Limassol and Larnaca. The coastline of the Mediterranean Sea lies to the south. Before 1974, substantial Cypriot-Turks lived here and they named it as "Terazi" ("Scales" in Turkish).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Cyprus_location_map.svg/250px-Cyprus_location_map.svg.png
